race.description: Long Lunch In The Grandview Marquee 28/02 Mdn Hcp
race.comment: It doesn't look a deep maiden and TASSALINA (3) looks better than average, tackling the line purpose in lead-up trial at Canberra. Drawn sticky but should have these covered. CHERRY JUBILEE (4) battled away gamely into fourth when resuming off a long break. Vulnerable to a flat effort second-up but is worth following up if she's come on from that. ROGUE NATION (1) is a Unite And Conqur gelding on debut for the Williams camp. Quietly readied with just the one soft Goulburn trial but has Heywood booked from a good draw. Have to monitor for market support. BLUE CATTLE DOG (5) got things back on track last time at Tumut when ridden more positive. Drawn well and can give backers a sight. SENSESATIONAL STAR (9) was too bad to be true last time over the 1500m at Albury. Her two runs prior were sound over sprinting trips, so expect a better performance this time.
